HEADWORD: Deuterogenic
<hw>Deu`ter*o*gen"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>deu`teros</grk> second + root of <grk>gi`gnesqai</grk> to be
born.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Of secondary origin; -- said of
certain rocks whose material has been derived from older
rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

